      "content": "okay that makes sense for a high level overview. but for the debate i really need to get deeper into the logic to make the affirmative case sound convincing. like, instead of just saying they wanted 'stability', can you elaborate on the specific arguments used regarding social cohesion or the idea that keeping certain groups separate actually helped prevent urban friction or social unrest? i need to be able to present these perspectives as coherent, rational strategies that planners and economists actually believed in at the time.",
